HEADWORD: Endoderm
<hw>En"do*derm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Endo-</ets> +
Gr. <?/ skin.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The inner
layer of the skin or integument of an animal.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The innermost layer of the blastoderm and the structures derived
from it; the hypoblast; the entoblast. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Ectoderm</er>.</def></p>

